The paper deals with planning problems in autonomous driving applications, which involve decision-making in continuous state and action spaces and interaction with multiple agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. The use of recurrent neural networks and supervised learning techniques further supports this. The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) aspects, as it involves modeling trajectories and predicting the near future based on the present. Finally, the paper deals with systems and control (cs.SY) aspects, as it involves optimizing long-term objectives and incorporating adversarial elements to the environment.
